**PLEASE NOTE ONLY APPLICATIONS WITH RESUME EMAILED DIRECTLY TO NYC-HR@MINBUZA.NL WILL BE ACCEPTED**

The Consulate General of the Netherlands in New York has a part-time vacancy **(16 hours per week, designated 4 morning hours for 4 days)** for a **Consular Officer**. This job will be offered at pay scale 6 for a fixed term of one year only, with a probationary period of one month. There will be no extension after one year (see job description below - English version only).

For more information about this vacancy,  
please contact Mr. Erwin Sluijter, e-mail: NYC-HR@minbuza.nl

Application letters with resume, both in English, must be addressed to:  
Consulate General of the Netherlands  
Attn: Mr. Erwin Sluijter, Manager Operations and Head of Consular Affairs  
and be submitted via email to: NYC-HR@minbuza.nl

Closing date for applications: August 7, 2024  
Starting date: as soon as possible.  
Indicative monthly gross salary: $ 2,506.00 (pay scale 6, step 0)

*\\* This vacancy is open to both internal candidates (local employees and partners of officials posted to a Mission in the US) and external candidates. If an external candidate and local candidate are equally qualified, the local candidate shall be given priority. Moreover, a local employee will be given priority over a partner of an official posted to a Mission in the US.*

*\\*\\*Candidates resident in the US need a valid working permit: US citizens, green card holders or G visa holders. Non-resident candidates can obtain a G visa.*

The consular officer is primarily responsible for providing consular services as well as some logistic, clerical and administrative support. The consular officer is the face of the Consulate General to the public, and therefore impeccable manners and customer service is imperative.

**Tasks**

**Consular services**

* Handling applications for travel documents, nationality requests, assessing the various documents, entering the applications in various computerised systems and issuing travel documents and visas, all according to the applicable rules and regulations;
* Providing background and other information and issuing guidelines and advice (orally and in writing) on applications for travel documents, visas and authorisations for temporary stay;
* Preparation of consular statements;
* Providing consular assistance and guidance to detained Dutch nationals in the area (contact, visit, reporting, etc.);
* Inform Dutch citizens about Governmental (travel) regulations and consular services in particular;
* In coordination with the Netherlands diplomatic network in the US develop and disseminate materials that increase the Consular services visibility among stakeholders;
* Assist in message development and social media content creation;
* All the above in an effective and customer-friendly manner.

**Logistical clerical support**

* Assessing the importance and urgency of incoming correspondence and, on his/her own initiative and at his/her own discretion, appending information that is needed in order to handle this in an adequate manner;
* Keeping consular records by creating, organising, storing, weeding and maintaining physical files and documents;
* Management of the daily cash proceeds and transfer to the account holder;
* Preparation of the (financial) accounting from the automated systems;
* Organizing, preparing and coordinating naturalization ceremonies.

**Support administrative / general affairs**

* Performing supportive administrative and logistical activities to aid one or more operational business processes in the field of business operations, including event management, transportation, simple translations and general administrative tasks that may occur. In cooperation with and under the guidance of the Operational manager.

**Framework**

* The Consular Officer is accountable to the Consul General for the accuracy of the information provided and the lawful application and implementation of the legislation, procedures and instructions in force;
* Relevant legislation, instructions and guidelines are important to performing duties properly;
* The consular affairs officer takes decisions about the provision of consular services as well as logistic clerical, communication and administrative support.

**Contacts**

* With members of the (Dutch) public;
* With third parties, to obtain and provide information on the content and progress of clerical processing of cases;
* With the Consular Service Organization (CSO) as a consular expertise centre and in the area of carrying out the back office tasks;
* With ministerial and inter-ministerial agencies/institutions, including the Consular Affairs and Migration Policy Department (DCV) and the Immigration and Naturalisation Service (IND), to provide or obtain further information;
* With the Netherlands consular and administrative network in the US.

**Knowledge and preferred skill requirements**

* Knowledge of applicable legislation, internal clerical and administrative procedures, work instructions and formal rules on competence and procedures, as well as the organisation’s duties, structure and way of working, or clear desire to learn;
* knowledge of general principles of policy concerning migration and consular affairs, or clear desire to learn;
* Well-developed skills in providing information on implementing legislation and procedures;
* knowledge in up to date communications strategy development;
* knowledge of digital marketing tactics, such as SEO and social media;
* a proven knowledge of the relevant computerised and other systems, social and communication skills.

**Competencies**

* Anticipating needs/requests;
* Customer focussed;
* Contact oriented;
* Collaboration;
* Quality oriented and results driven;
* Integer;
* Stress resistant.

**Level of education / Additional training and knowledge**

* Secondary vocational level;
* some experience is preferred;
* outstanding social and communication skills;
* fluent, orally and in writing, in the English language required,
* fluent, orally and in writing, in the Dutch language strongly preferred.

**Work Environment**

The Consulate General (CG) in New York is a diplomatic mission with 5 expats and 16 local employees. The CG is active in the fields of trade, foreign direct investment, promotion of the Dutch culture and public diplomacy.

In the consular field, the Consulate General focuses on promoting the interests of the Dutch citizens and on implementing the passport and visa policy.

The CG is a close-knit enthusiastic team, within which the various employees are responsible for the correct and timely handling of the work assigned to them. This means that all employees are expected to go beyond the boundaries of their own area of ​​responsibility, to pay attention to the functioning of the CG as a whole and to assist colleagues with high work pressure. The coordination of activities of the consular affairs officer takes place under the responsibility of the Consul General.

**Staff Member Profile**

* You are able to work independently as well as in a team and you have good social and communication skills;
* You are reliable, customer-friendly, creative, solution and result-oriented and you have a flexible and positive attitude;
* You are able to remain friendly under all circumstances while being firm on rules and regulations. A high level of integrity is a must and you will not succumb to pressure;
* And last but certainly not least: you are a an enthusiastic person who likes to work in a vibrant team and is open to learn.

The Netherlands Government celebrates all forms of diversity and is deeply committed to foster an inclusive environment within its organization. Individuals interested in advancing these diversity goals are strongly encouraged to apply.

