The Permanent Mission of the Netherlands to the United Nations in New York has a fulltime (40 hours per week) local vacancy for a Secretary/Administrative Assistant to the Political Department. Additional information regarding this position is available – by email only – from Mr. Erwin Sluijter, at NYV-HR@minbuza.nl.

Please send your application, with resume, to:  
Permanent Mission of the Kingdom of the Netherlands to the United Nations  
Attn. Mr. Erwin Sluijter  
666 Third Avenue, 19th floor  
New York, NY 10017  
USA

e-mail: NYV-HR@minbuza.nl

Closing date for applications: 14 August 2024  
Starting Date: 1 October 2024

Indicative monthly gross salary (based on pay scale New York, scale 5, pay step 0): $5,433.00 gross per month.

\\* This vacancy is open to both internal candidates (local employees and partners of officials posted to a Mission in the US) and external candidates. If an external candidate and local candidate are equally qualified, the local candidate shall be given priority. Moreover, a local employee will be given priority over a partner of an official posted to a Mission in the US.

\\*\\*Candidates resident in the US need a valid working permit: US citizens, green card holders or G visa holders. Non-resident candidates can obtain a G visa.

**General features of the job**

* Your job will have three main elements: 1. to provide secretarial and administrative support to the Political Affairs and Communication Department of the Permanent Mission; 2. Assist the Election Officer of the Mission with election campaigns within the UN system; 3. Assist the Legal Advisor of the Mission with legal correspondence.
* You work under the supervision of the (Deputy) Head of Department and the Election Officer and work closely with a number of policy officers. You’ll also work closely together with the other Secretary/Administrative Assistants in the Mission. The Head of Department will secure the quality and the progress of the administrative tasks and support. Your work will be carried out in accordance with departmental administrative and procedural rules, requirements and work agreements.
* The team has an extensive external network (UN, other missions) and you enjoy expanding your networks and relations.
* Careful handling of confidential subjects and files is a must.
* General interest in, and knowledge of, UN work and political affairs is a bonus.
* You determine the urgency and importance of the tasks, such as correspondence, preparing and reporting meetings, scheduling appointments, and collecting and organizing information and files. You’re able and enjoy to act proactively and individually.
* During peak moments (such as the yearly High Level Week of the UN General Assembly) the workload can be intense and will require work outside of normal business hours (overtime will be compensated).

**Duties and result areas**

This vacancy concerns an assistant position of 40 hours a week at the Political Affairs and Communication Department. At the Mission there are 3 assistant positions (including this position) who are all dedicated to specific tasks of the different departments, but are each capable to replace each other. Depending on supply and demand of the Mission, tasks can and will be distributed among the 3 assistants. Assuming duties temporarily of the receptionist is also an important part of the duties.

**Description of duties**

* Secretarial/administrative support to the Policy Officers, amongst others, by organizing and preparing meetings, maintaining a strong network within the UN Secretariat, other Permanent Missions in New York and the Ministry of Foreign Affairs in The Hague;
* Handling incoming and outgoing mail, including forwarding documents and letters to the Ministry in The Hague;
* Organizing and facilitating of visitors programs for (high-level) visitors from the Capital;
* Elaboration of letters, Note Verbales, memoranda, a. o., both instructed by Policy Officers from the Political Department and the Election Officer, as well as on own initiative;
* Preparing and sending invitations for official gatherings and maintaining the guestlist;
* Scheduling appointments for the Policy Officers of the Political Affairs and Communication Department;
* Managing information related to UN elections and assisting in election work and events;
* Welcoming visitors;
* Logistical support when organizing side events, at the Mission, the UN, Residence and external locations;
* Organization of catering for breakfast and lunch meetings and receptions;
* Other administrative work;
* Taking meeting minutes;
* Replace of other secretaries when absent;
* Replace of the receptionist when absent;
* Managing elections mailbox;
* Monitor the progress of tasks and, where necessary, send reminders.

**Working environment**

The Permanent Mission represents the Kingdom of the Netherlands at the United Nations in New York. We promote and defend the interests and values ​​of our Kingdom in the strong belief that effective multilateral cooperation is crucial to address global challenges in the areas of peace and security, sustainable development, rule of law, accountability and human rights. We are a reliable partner working with others to build a stronger UN system as part of the solution to global challenges. We are committed to operating with integrity, professionalism, respect, diversity and inclusion as our core principles. Approximately 41 employees work at the Mission, including trainees and interns.

You will be part of the Political and Communications Department. This department consists of a head (also Deputy Permanent Representative), deputy head, and 9 policy officers. This department also interacts with the Development, Humanitarian Affairs and Human Rights Department and the Military and Police Affairs Department. The formal supervisor is the head of the Political Affairs and Communication Department/DPR.

The Mission is, together with the Consulate General and the Netherlands Foreign Investment Agency, located in a modern high-rise building within walking distance from the United Nations Headquarters.

The Mission has several peak moments during the year due to conferences, visitors, meetings and other activities.

During the high season of the HLPF and General Assembly of the United Nations (July and September) it might happen that the Secretary/Administrative Assistant works from 8:00 – 20:00 in shifts, together with other assistants.

Composition of the Mission in which you will be working:

* Permanent Representative and Deputy Permanent Representative;
* Four heads of departments (Development, Humanitarian Affairs and Human Rights Section, Political Affairs and Communication Department, Military and Police Affairs Department and Shared Services Desk);
* The Shared Services Desk consists of the Manager Operations, two Deputy Manager Operations, two Senior General Affairs Officers, one IT officer, one IT assistant, one receptionist/clerical officer, three facility officers and one cleaner;
* Several temporary staff members during the whole year;
* Frequently incoming (high-level) visitors.

**Competencies**

The candidate must possess the following competences:

* Client orientation;
* Excellent communication/writing skills in both English and Dutch;
* Ability to work with others;
* Adaptability, flexibility & initiative;
* Organisational sensitivity;
* Stress resistant;
* Ability to plan and organize
* Representative

**Knowledge and skills**

Level of education: Vocational education  
Level of experience: minimum of 1-4 years’ work experience

* Excellent organizational skills: ensuring quick and careful follow-up of duties and tasks;
* Broad knowledge of management assistance methods, organizational/logistic/ administrative regulations;
* Understanding of/having a feel for diplomatic contacts and functional relationships of the Mission with third parties and the way of working of the Mission;
* Skilled in setting priorities regarding the different support tasks and weighing up consequences, interests etc.;
* Skilled in drafting letters, minutes, notes and reports etc. and performing tasks regarding data storage and archiving;
* Skilled in working under varying conditions and time pressure;
* Skilled in Windows-driven MS Office programs such as Word, Excel, Outlook and PowerPoint;
* Skilled in using social media like X and LinkedIn;
* Good command of written and oral communication skills in the English and Dutch languages;

**Contacts**

* With third parties within and outside the Mission about secretarial and administrative proceedings, exchange of information about the content and progress of these proceedings and to arrange meetings;
* Weekly meetings on UN-elections with counterparts in The Ministry of Foreign Affairs in The Hague, The Netherlands.

The Netherlands’ Government celebrates all forms of diversity and is deeply committed to foster an inclusive environment within its organization. Individuals interested in advancing these diversity goals are strongly encouraged to apply.

